-- Saudi Arabia Might Require Banks to Lend to SMEs, Hayat Reports
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2012-03-04T06:34:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-04/saudi-arabia-might-require-banks-to-lend-to-smes-hayat-reports.html
Saudi Arabia  might require banks to
allocate part of their loans to small- and medium-sized
businesses,  al-Hayat  reported, citing Labor Minister Adel Faqih.
The kingdom may also allow establishment of banks dedicated to
SME lending, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
